    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-02-22T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-02-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="384"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/653: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-22T16:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 22, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 23—1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Election finished. Legation latest returns are over 168,000 for General
                    Orellana the only official candidate, and about 400 scattering.</p>
                <p>In addition to the disturbances reported in my telegram February 7 [<hi
                        rend="italic">17</hi>], 5 p.m.,<note n="3" xml:id="d384fn3">Not
                        printed.</note> there was an uprising at Escuintla on Saturday night with at
                    least 7 killed. Apparently there has [<hi rend="italic">have</hi>] been no other
                    disorders of this sort.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
